'''The Afghan Institute for Strategic Studies''' ('''AISS''') is an Afghan-based [[think tank]] in [[Kabul]], [[Afghanistan]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/opinion/2016/08/afghanistan-political-crisis-entitlement-democracy-160813140531295.html|title=Afghanistan political crisis: Entitlement vs democracy|website=www.aljazeera.com|access-date=2017-01-11}}</ref> The AISS established in October 2012 to address the strategic issues pertaining to [[Afghanistan]] in the wider regional and international contexts.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/column-mending-asia-s-heart-tackling-terror-together-2278909|title=Mending Asia’s heart: Tackling terror together {{!}} Latest News & Updates at Daily News & Analysis|date=2016-12-02|newspaper=dna|language=en-US|access-date=2017-01-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/features/2016/11/afghans-weigh-presidential-candidates-161106034333699.html|title=Afghans weigh in on US presidential candidates|website=www.aljazeera.com|access-date=2017-01-11}}</ref> The AISS provides policy-oriented research, publication, translation of books/reports, professional training and policy advocacy with distinct focus on Afghanistan. Dr. [[Davood Moradian]] is currently Director of AISS.

