{{BLP refimprove|date=September 2018}} {{Infobox criminal |image_name = Replace this image male.svg <!-- only free-content images are allowed for depicting living people - see [[WP:NONFREE]] --> | | name = Michael Bray | image_size = | image_caption = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | charge = conspiracy and possessing unregistered explosive devices in relation to 10 different bomb attacks | conviction_penalty = 10 years | conviction_status = served 46 months from 1985 to 1989; living in [[Wilmington, Ohio]] since December 2003 | occupation = | spouse = Jayne Bray (1976 - present) | children = 11}}
Rev. '''Michael Bray''' is an [[United States|American]] [[Lutheran]] minister who was convicted in 1985 of two counts of conspiracy and one count of possessing unregistered explosive devices in relation to ten bombings of women's health clinics and offices of liberal advocacy groups in [[Washington, D.C.]], [[Maryland]] and [[Virginia]].<ref>''News in Brief'' [[The Times]] 23 May 1985</ref> He is considered "the intellectual father of the extreme radical fringe of the [[pro-life|antiabortion]] movement which engages in terrorism."<ref name=stern>{{cite book|last=Stern|first=Jessica|title=Terror in the name of God: why religious militants kill|year=2003|publisher=[[HarperCollins]]|location=New York|isbn=0-06-050533-8|pages=148|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=13iAVXvu6jQC&lpg=PA148&dq=michael%20bray%20terrorist&pg=PA148#v=onepage&q&f=false|authorlink=Jessica Stern|accessdate=6 January 2012}}</ref> Initially sentenced to ten years in prison, he agreed to a [[plea bargain]] and served 46 months from 1985 to 1989. <!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Michael Bray Anti-Abortion Sign.jpg|thumb|Michael Bray holds anti-abortion sign outside courthouse where James Kopp is on trial for shooting abortionist Barnett Slepian.]] -->
He and his wife, Jayne, are named defendants in the [[SCOTUS|Supreme Court]] decision [[Bray v. Alexandria Women's Health Clinic|''Bray v. Alexandria'']]. He is considered to be a terrorist by the National Memorial Institute for the Prevention of Terrorism.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tkb.org/KeyLeader.jsp?memID=25|title=The MIPT Terrorism Knowledge Base|publisher=|accessdate=27 November 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930041239/http://www.tkb.org/KeyLeader.jsp?memID=25#|archive-date=2007-09-30|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref>
In 1994, the [[F.B.I.]] suspected that he and other anti-abortion figures might be developing "a conspiracy that endeavors to achieve political or social change through activities that involve force or violence", as stated in a confidential [[Teletype Corporation|Teletype]] message sent to all 56 F.B.I. field offices.<ref>{{Citation | last = Johnston | first = David | author-link = | title = F.B.I. Undertakes Conspiracy Inquiry In Clinic Violence | newspaper = [[New York Times]] | pages = | year = | date = August 4, 1994 | url = https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9F0DEFD71231F937A3575BC0A962958260&sec=&spon=&pagewanted=print}}</ref>
==Background== Michael Bray is a former [[Midshipman]] at the [[United States Naval Academy]].<ref name=samuels>{{cite news | last = Samuels | first = David | title = The Making of a Fugitive | newspaper = [[New York Times Magazine]] | date = March 21, 1999 | url = https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9E06EFD8103EF932A15750C0A96F958260&scp=21&sq=%22michael+bray%22&st=nyt }}</ref> He was based in [[Bowie, Maryland]], and later moved to [[Wilmington, Ohio]], where he professes to be a member of the [[Army of God (USA)|Army of God]], considered a terrorist organization<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fbi.gov/libref/factsfigure/counterterrorism.htm# |title=Archived copy |access-date=2016-07-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161223182153/https://www2.fbi.gov/libref/factsfigure/counterterrorism.htm# |archive-date=2016-12-23 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> by the US Federal Bureau of Investigation. Bray's writings can be found on the Army of God website.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.armyofgod.com/MikeBrayIndex.html# |title=Archived copy |access-date=2018-11-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181029023530/https://www.armyofgod.com/MikeBrayIndex.html# |archive-date=2018-10-29 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref>
